---
description: Controller file-structure conventions for this repo. Apply when creating or editing controller files under images/state-snapshotter-controller/internal/controllers/.
globs: images/state-snapshotter-controller/internal/controllers/**/*.go
alwaysApply: false
---

- Controller files (MUST):
  - Keep per-controller reconciliation logic in a single `<name>_controller.go`.
  - `Reconcile(...)` and `SetupWithManager(...)` live in the same file.

- In-file sections (SHOULD):
  - Keep clear sections in `<name>_controller.go`:
    - `// SetupWithManager` (wiring only: watches/predicates/options).
    - `// Reconcile` (orchestration).
    - `// Helpers` (supporting functions).

- Patch-base discipline (MUST):
  - Before any patch/update, capture a base copy (`base := obj.DeepCopy()`).
  - Patch using the base to avoid clobbering unrelated fields.

- Job idempotency (MUST):
  - If the controller creates **Jobs** or similar ephemeral resources, identify them by **labels** (and optional owner refs), not by name alone — names may be deterministic but are not the sole contract.
  - Cleanup selectors MUST be restart-safe (label-based). Any label keys MUST be constants in `pkg/snapshot` or spec (`docs/state-snapshotter-rework/spec/system-spec.md`).

- Shared code placement (SHOULD):
  - Shared helpers go to `helpers.go`.
  - Shared constants go to `constants.go`.
  - Shared errors go to `errors.go`.

- Avoid structural drift (MUST NOT):
  - Do NOT introduce a split `controller.go` / `reconciler.go` layout in this repo.
